{
  "texts": [
    "It can be applied to various real-world applications, such as drones and mobile robotics (Taketomi et al., 2017).",
    "The integration of IMU data enhances and augments the information available for environment modeling, resulting in improved accuracy and reduced errors within the system's functioning (Macario Barros et al., 2022; Mur-Artal and Tardós 2017b).",
    "The methods and algorithms used in this approach, while implemented in real-life applications, can be listed as shown in the following section.",
    "OKVIS-SLAM, which stands for open keyframe-based visual-inertial SLAM, is designed for robotics and computer vision applications that require real-time 3D reconstruction, object tracking, and position estimation (Kasyanov et al., 2017).",
    "It combines visual and inertial measurements to accurately predict the position and orientation of a robot simultaneously (Leut et al., 2015)."
  ]
}